ANIMATE A LINKS
you can use [a:hover, a:active, a:link, a:visited]
can be written as...

a:active{
   color: green
   background-color: transparent; 
   text-decoration: none or underline;
}

this describe reaching in the parent <li>
and high (link) child element <a href=""></a>
li a:hover {
    background-color: #111111;
}

IMG

-for regular img in another file
 <img scr="/file/image.type(png,gif,orjpg)">

----------------------------------------------
-this makes an image that has places on it where you can click.

 <img src="workplace.jpg" alt="Workplace" usemap="#workmap">

<!--this is the map that set the places on the image where you can click-->

<map name="workmap">
  <area shape="rect" coords="34,44,270,350" alt="Computer" href="computer.htm">

  <area shape="rect" coords="290,172,333,250" alt="Phone" href="phone.htm">
  
  <area shape="circle" coords="337,300,44" alt="Coffee" href="coffee.htm">
</map>
-----------TYPES OF LISTS------------------
list-style-type: disc/circle/square/none
they help describe how the <li> item is presented:

UNORGANIZED LIST
<ul style="list-style-type:disc">
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>
ORGANIZED 
 <ol>
 </ol>
 
DESCRIPTIVE LIST
<dl>
  <dt>Coffee</dt>
  <dd>- black hot drink</dd>
  <dt>Milk</dt>
  <dd>- white cold drink</dd>
</dl>

